body.name: CORSAIR Hydro X Series XC7 RGB PRO CPU Water Block for Intel LGA 1700, 1200, 115X and AMD Socket AM4 (Copper Cold Plate, 110 MicroCooling Fins, 5V ARGB Motherboard Adapter Cable Included) White
deliveryMessages: Or fastest delivery Wednesday, February 14. Order within 14 hrs 31 mins

features: A precision-machined nickel-plated copper cold plate with more than 110 high-efficiency micro-cooling fins, combined with an innovative quad-split flow design, efficiently draws heat away from your CPU, reducing temperatures by up to 4°C lower than the previous generation XC7 RGB.
Built from durable nylon with reinforced standard G1/4” threads, the XC7 RGB PRO will keep your CPU running at its best, and coolest, for years to come.

16 Individually addressable RGB LEDs deliver 360° of stunning customizable RGB lighting effects. Add a CORSAIR iCUE Controller (sold separately) and powerful CORSAIR iCUE software to customize and sync RGB lighting across all your iCUE-compatible products including other water blocks, pumps, fans, keyboard, and more.
A transparent flow chamber shows off your coolant and enhances RGB lighting, with a titanium matte white trim that matches the modern aesthetic of other white CORSAIR products in your setup.
Includes a 5V ARGB motherboard adapter cable to alternatively control lighting via compatible motherboards.
Easy and fast installation on Intel LGA 1700, LGA 1200, LGA 115X, or AMD Socket AM4 with pre-installed mounting screws and pre-applied thermal material.
body.description: The CORSAIR Hydro X Series XC7 RGB PRO CPU Water Block combines premium construction, vivid RGB lighting, a titanium matte white trim, and extraordinary cooling performance thanks to an advanced nickel-plated copper cold plate, innovative quad-split flow design, and more than 110 high-efficiency micro-cooling fins. 16 Individually addressable RGB LEDs deliver 360° of customizable RGB lighting, controllable with a CORSAIR iCUE RGB Lighting Controller or with compatible motherboards.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Yes, you can rotate the display
reviews.reviewText: I have used many types of waterblocks in many open loop systems over the years, and I can say the cooling performance is very good on this block. Is it the absolute best? No, but the difference is small, and if you're using this, you're getting it for the screen anyway, not premium thermal performance. The good news is that it works well. Apparently when these launched you couldn't rotate the display in iCue, but you can now and it's easy. One thing to note is that while iCue is running it's going to display temps, which I like, and it will play the fun gifs when iCue closes, so startup and shut down, unless you keep the gif menu open, then it will loop for as long as you want. In practice this makes a lot of sense, I think a gif looping all the time would get old pretty fast. Anyway, it's very fun, and it's easy to set up.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful and easy to install
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Easy to install in the sense that Corsair provides a guiding bracket/frame and instructions on how to mount to the CPU -- was super helpful!! 😂 also, they have a layer of thermal paste evenly pre-applied, so as long as you don't do something crazy (or unless you want better paste and replace it yourself), you can easily mount it with very little prior experience.In terms of visual appeal and overall quality of materials I am very happy with this purchase!!! It adds such a nice element to the build and does a great job keeping my CPU temp in check. It can be a bit of a daunting task getting everything in order for a Corsair build, but it's so worth it!!! Thank you Corsair for keeping quality *and* aesthetic appeal top of mind!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works well, looks great
reviews.reviewText: This product does exactly what it's suppose to do. It's beautiful when it's lit up and it was very easy to install. Temps seem to be steady when the PC is running. Overall I have no issues and would gladly use again on another build.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works fine, looks good
reviews.reviewText: Got it for my existing 3 years old Corsair custom water loop. Fits ok, works with my old Commander Pro, works with the new iCUE software. Though it says you can install it any direction you want on an Intel, I had the best results when installed vertically, with the arrow down (corsair logo on the left) when looking at the CPU aligned vertically. This orientation won't let it trap air bubbles.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Looks amazing and temps are great
reviews.reviewText: The screen on the block looks amazing and is crystal clear, temps are perfect on my 5800x3d, I took 1 star off since corsair told me I would need a LINK hub to make the screen work... this is not true, it comes with a usb-c to usb internal 2.0 header

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great, no complaints.
reviews.reviewText: One of the few affordable un-plated liquid blocks. I have a pretty beefy setup for a mini PC,+liquid metal, but this does help to keep the temps of my 14900K down to around 88-89* at full tilt. My only gripe is I wish the screws were actual screws instead of hand screws. It's next to impossible to twist them in a small case, and keeping the torque even is difficult, if not possible.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works well and looks cool
reviews.reviewText: I wasn't expecting the LEDs to also glow onto the motherboard, but this thing is really cool looking, it works really well too. I wanted to add the CPU to my GPU custom water loop and added another radiator at the same time and am very happy with how corsairs systems all work together. iCUE has helped me cool my computer and build my custom loop with ease. So long as I was able to get the hardware in the right place, they were able to handle the software well.

reviews.reviewTitle: Solid and easy to install. Worked with my G1/4 thread system. Smooth and no leaks.
reviews.reviewText: I used this for to add on to a custom water cooling system.\

This block is quite large. The circular mounting bracket requires a lot of clearance. My Gigabyte X570 Master is not compatible due to a row of capacitors that are in the way of the mounting bracket.Wish this was documented or advertised somewhere. If they used a different mounting system other than this locking ring bracket it would have worked.Check the clearance around the socket if you're planning on buying this water block.

The media could not be loaded. Da ich den Kühler so ungefähr zum Release Zeitpunkt erstanden habe hatte ich das Tal der Tränen durchlaufen müssen, aber die Software Fehler sind heutzutage Behoben und ich bin recht happy mit dem Artikel.Der Feler der mich am längsten triggerte, war das man die Orientierung noch einstellen konnte. Heutzutage ist es ja kein Problem mehr, aber ich musste für die Zeit eben meine Videos 90° drehen und konnte damals auch nur diese Video nutze, denn alles andere war eben um 90° zur Seite gekippt.Einen Kritikpunkt habe ich aber noch, der Temperatursensor. Denn was er misst ist weder Fisch noch Fleisch, da er weder die Temperatur des CPU noch die des Wassers an dem Punkt des Loop erfasst. Denn meine Wassertemperatur wird von meiner Pumpe, am Ausgang der GPU, dann vom XC7 und nach den Radiatoren noch vom Flowmesser zum Reservoir hin. Bei allen anderen 3 Sensoren liegt der Wert bis auf ein Grad gleich. Aber da ja weder das Wasser noch die CPU selbst mit dem Sensor gemessen wird kommt im XC7 immer ein Wert der mindestens 5 Grad mehr zeigt heraus.

Etant passé d'un socket AM4 à un AM5 et pas certain que mon waterblock XC7 pour AM4 soit compatible, j'ai opté pour ce nouveau modèle, encore plus beau et aussi performant d'après les nombreux tests que j'ai pu lire.Package très complet, tous les adaptateurs pour les sockets Intel ou AMD récents sont fournis, le tout de belle facture. Comme souvent avec Corsair, les pièces respirent la qualité.Malheureusement, je n'ai pas prêté attention au fait que l'alimentation du RGB ne soit pas standard (3 pins 5V ou 4 pins 12V) mais propre à Corsair avec son nouveau système iCue Link. J'ai eu beau cherché sur le Net, pas moyen de trouver un câble adaptateur. Il faut nécessairement acheté le système iCue et installer le logiciel de Corsair pour le faire fonctionner, ce qui est hors de question vu que ce logiciel entre en conflit avec Armoury Crate (j'ai une CM Asus).Par conséquent, je me retrouve avec un WB très efficace mais... éteint :(
